      "created_at": "2016-06-07 18:52:15 UTC",
      "updated_at": "2016-06-07 18:53:13 UTC",
      "body": "As a counter-point…  Hocon is an incredibly annoying configuration format.  :-)  It's better than JSON, but I've just had universally massively negative experiences with it.  YAML is very lightweight, and its only negative aspects are a) hard to write a fully-compliant parser, and b) association with Rails.\r\n\r\nVerizon uses YAML internally quite extensively, and it appears that we primarily use the following dependency:\r\n\r\n```sbt\r\nlibraryDependencies += \"org.yaml\" % \"snakeyaml\" % \"1.16\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nNot the prettiest API to work with, but it does work.  I would assume that Knobs has support for it, since that is our project.  :-)  That would make it easier to work with.\r\n\r\nWhy does scalafmt need to be Scala.js compatible?"
    },
