      "created_at": "2016-06-07 19:44:17 UTC",
      "updated_at": "2016-06-07 19:44:17 UTC",
      "body": "My biggest concern is bringing in a massive dependency on a configuration library when scalafmt only needs the most basic features. There's no need for dates, environment variables, system properties, imports/config loading from other files, automatic reloading on resource change (although that might be nice for the IntelliJ plugin), etc.\r\n\r\nThing is scalafmt configuration files should stay tiny, max 5 lines IMO. If you need more than that I think we should reconsider the provided styles. For large organizations like Verizon I'm happy to make `--style verizon` a thing."
    },
