      "created_at": "2016-06-07 20:24:34 UTC",
      "updated_at": "2016-06-07 20:24:34 UTC",
      "body": "True, scalafmt may accumulate quite a big selection of options. Still, most users shouldn't deviate too far from a provided base style. I imagine this is the case for ClangFormat, which probably has 80+ options and an excellent selection of base styles.\r\n\r\nI'm still leaning more towards shocon because of Scala.js compat (that browser extension is gonna be so cool 😄). From what I can tell, shocon only depends on fastparse, which scalafmt already depends on transitively via scala.meta for XML literal parsing."
    },
