      "created_at": "2016-06-08 07:17:23 UTC",
      "updated_at": "2016-06-08 07:17:23 UTC",
      "body": "Seems like YAML is popular, I'm happy to reconsider.\r\n\r\n@sjrd makes an interesting suggestion, we still don't even know if/when scala.meta will support Scala.js. When the time comes, it seems like js-yaml could solve our problems: http://nodeca.github.io/js-yaml/ \r\n\r\nI also saw suggested on twitter that it's possible use snakeyaml via [jackson](https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-dataformat-yaml) via [circe](https://github.com/travisbrown/circe). Not sure if that's the way to go but it's worth a look. Thanks for the input everybody.\r\n"
