  "closed_at": null,
  "body": "Following discussions on Gitter: https://gitter.im/olafurpg/scalafmt?at=5755e80492fc7c915f574b06\r\n\r\nThe current configuration is built on scopt and is quite hacky: https://olafurpg.github.io/scalafmt/#Configuration\r\nIt would be great to use a more standard syntax.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n* Scala.js compatible\r\n* supports comments\r\n* not verbose\r\n* allows multiple configurations on same line, like `a=1;b=2`. See #315\r\n\r\nConsidered options:\r\n* [shocon](https://github.com/unicredit/shocon) seems like a perfect fit. @andreaTP, are there any docs/non-SNAPSHOT releases?\r\n* typesafe config: no Scala.js support.\r\n* http://oncue.github.io/knobs/: can't see Scala.js support.\r\n* YAML: Don't think there's any Scala.js implementation."
